      "writtenOn": "2026-03-05T17:19:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, I agree.\nThe `async_wait` where the signal is processed is wrapped in the meson option `persist-settings-to-file`. \nBut if the handling of signal is also wrapped, then when a reload is fired for `service-config-manager`, due to the changes made in service file to send a `SIGHUP` signal, it will execute it\u0027s default behavior - to terminate the service. The maximum tries to restart on termination is 3, after that the the service will be deactivated.",
      "parentUuid": "c6c2979a_86c608aa",
      "revId": "6e78ffc58c11d49fa6554de115273ad90a41dcf8",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
